_

08:15.256 --> 08:17.332
No, we're gonna make this work.

08:17.366 --> 08:20.480
We just need to figure it out, that's all.

08:20.500 --> 08:23.180
You and I are gonna be together.

08:25.265 --> 08:26.864
I love Wes.

08:26.884 --> 08:29.944
He said that you will not
be implicated in any way.

08:29.979 --> 08:31.029
Thank you so much.

08:31.049 --> 08:34.883
I know it must have been hard for you
to ask him for this.

08:34.917 --> 08:38.568
Now look, we really dodged a bullet here.

08:38.589 --> 08:39.921
You have to promise me...

08:39.955 --> 08:42.789
That nothing like this
will ever happen again.

08:42.825 --> 08:44.298
You have my word.

08:47.252 --> 08:49.262
Come on, let's go tell John and Kathryn.

08:49.282 --> 08:52.238
They've been so worried since I told them
about what I did.

08:52.258 --> 08:53.789
- Let's go.
- Yes.

08:58.614 --> 09:00.375
- (Laughs)
- (Sighs)

09:01.977 --> 09:06.047
- What's going on?
- This is Detective Markham.

09:06.345 --> 09:07.735
Is something wrong?

09:07.755 --> 09:10.084
She's here to arrest you.

09:13.820 --> 09:17.143
John: Okay, so what exactly
kind of trouble are we in here?

09:17.887 --> 09:19.262
I don't have all the details yet,

09:19.282 --> 09:22.265
but they have physical evidence placing
Daphne at the scene of the crime.

09:22.285 --> 09:24.328
- How did they find out?
- I don't know yet.

09:24.348 --> 09:26.536
I'll be getting all that information
as a matter of discovery,

09:26.556 --> 09:29.582
but the big issue here is that
Daphne is still under probation,

09:29.617 --> 09:31.497
which means that if she's convicted of
these charges,

09:31.517 --> 09:34.354
- it constitutes a second strike.
- No, no, no, wait a second.

09:34.388 --> 09:38.251
Okay, she was under 18
when the first strike happened...

09:38.271 --> 09:40.596
I thought you said Wes worked this out.
What happened?

09:40.616 --> 09:42.468
Honestly, I don't know.

09:42.488 --> 09:45.831
That plus the probation violation,

09:45.851 --> 09:47.967
Daphne will be looking at doing some time.

09:48.002 --> 09:50.782
- You mean prison?
- That can't happen.

09:50.802 --> 09:54.941
Normal sentencing guidelines would
dictate a three-year prison sentence.

09:54.975 --> 09:56.308
Three years?

09:56.328 --> 09:58.293
She'd never have to do the full three.

09:58.313 --> 10:01.296
- More likely a year and a half.
- (Gasps)

10:01.520 --> 10:03.808
- Oh, my God.
- No, absolutely not.

10:03.828 --> 10:07.213
What about this kid Nacho?
Where the hell is he in all of this?

10:07.233 --> 10:10.076
They have a warrant out for his arrest,
but presently they have no leads.

10:10.096 --> 10:11.937
Essentially he's vanished,

10:11.957 --> 10:14.494
but that's of little
relevance for Daphne's case.

10:14.528 --> 10:16.563
- Why not?
- Because the D.A. is more interested

10:16.597 --> 10:19.332
in a high-profile conviction
of a state senator's daughter.

10:19.366 --> 10:21.987
And they'll be looking for someone
to pay restitution for damages.

10:22.007 --> 10:24.717
And that someone is Daphne.

10:25.101 --> 10:27.440
- We're gonna fight this.
- We'll pay the damages.

10:27.474 --> 10:30.875
We're gonna go to trial.
We're gonna fight this all the way.

10:30.895 --> 10:33.803
Okay, that's an option,
and we'll assess the merits of a trial

10:33.823 --> 10:37.574
once I get the full discovery, but what you
have to remember is that if Daphne loses,

10:37.594 --> 10:40.577
and I firmly believe that
she could very well lose,

10:40.597 --> 10:43.741
she'd be looking at the
full three years in prison.

10:44.759 --> 10:46.603
I understand you're all upset right now,

10:46.623 --> 10:48.795
and there are no great
options on the table,

10:48.829 --> 10:51.497
but I have a solid
relationship with this D.A.,

10:51.517 --> 10:53.619
and I could get Daphne a plea deal.

10:53.639 --> 10:56.938
If you pay restitution
and plead no contest,

10:56.958 --> 10:58.174
I could get her six months.

10:58.194 --> 11:01.190
With good behavior,
she'd be back home in 90 days.

11:01.910 --> 11:03.788
Ninety days.

11:03.808 --> 11:05.464
Now, she'd still have a record.

11:05.484 --> 11:07.547
That is not going to work. I'm sorry.

11:07.581 --> 11:09.040
We're gonna get a different lawyer.

11:09.060 --> 11:11.751
I'm gonna do whatever it takes.

11:11.931 --> 11:14.240
That's certainly your prerogative,

11:14.438 --> 11:17.905
but what I want you all
to understand is this...

11:17.925 --> 11:20.050
no matter what you do,

11:20.070 --> 11:22.953
Daphne will do some time.

11:33.036 --> 11:35.096
So let me get this straight.

11:35.116 --> 11:37.789
Because I don't sleep with you,
you turn my daughter in?

11:37.809 --> 11:38.798
What are you talking about?

11:38.818 --> 11:41.280
I just finished bailing Daphne out of jail,

11:41.300 --> 11:43.420
and now they're bringing her up on charges.

11:43.440 --> 11:45.213
It looks like she's going to prison.

11:45.233 --> 11:46.185
Thank you!

11:46.220 --> 11:48.187
Well, I swear. I didn't do anything.

11:48.222 --> 11:52.200
Really? Because you are the only one
who knew about her involvement in this.

11:52.220 --> 11:54.321
Look,
anyone could have found out what happened.

11:54.341 --> 11:55.562
- Just because...
- Save it.

11:55.582 --> 11:59.203
You gave me your word,
and that meant something to me,

11:59.223 --> 12:01.077
but obviously I was an idiot,

12:01.097 --> 12:03.083
because you will always be the Wes Gable

12:03.103 --> 12:07.407
that puts yourself,
your money and your business first.

12:08.409 --> 12:09.833
Regina.

12:09.853 --> 12:11.511
(Sighs)

12:11.545 --> 12:13.142
(Knock on door)

12:15.516 --> 12:16.751
What took you so long?

12:16.771 --> 12:19.029
Tank's gonna be here in an hour, so...

12:19.049 --> 12:21.859
Can I get a rain check?
Being that I just got sacked,

12:21.879 --> 12:24.257
I'm not really in that kind of mood.

12:25.842 --> 12:27.160
Sure.

12:27.194 --> 12:30.424
Sorry, I wasn't thinking.

12:31.429 --> 12:35.405
So have you given any thought

12:35.425 --> 12:37.194
to what's next for you?

12:37.214 --> 12:40.842
Not really, but I like being back home.

12:41.450 --> 12:43.560
I think I'll try and make a go of it.

12:43.783 --> 12:46.737
That doesn't have anything to do with me,
right?

12:46.757 --> 12:47.770
I mean,

12:47.790 --> 12:51.448
do we need to talk about what this is?

12:51.468 --> 12:54.141
Like a state of the union?

12:54.161 --> 12:56.586
We fight and then we bonk.

12:56.606 --> 12:58.148
Not necessarily in that order.

12:58.168 --> 13:01.861
That is our union fully stated.

13:02.157 --> 13:05.189
I'm not staying here because of you.
I like it here.

13:05.209 --> 13:08.521
Good. You know, 'cause I just got out

13:08.541 --> 13:11.044
of this complicated marriage and...

13:11.064 --> 13:13.673
Toby, I like it just the way it is.

13:13.707 --> 13:16.252
Friends with the occasional bonking.

13:16.272 --> 13:18.444
The bonking is good.

13:18.479 --> 13:19.941
Yeah.

13:20.481 --> 13:22.615
Well, it's been a pretty crap day.

13:22.649 --> 13:24.682
So I think I'll push off.

13:26.453 --> 13:30.144
I'll see you tomorrow at graduation then,
as friends.

13:30.913 --> 13:32.564
See you there.

13:34.810 --> 13:37.843
So apparently the police were able

13:37.863 --> 13:41.402
to lift Daphne's fingerprints
from the damaged tractor.

13:41.422 --> 13:43.269
And because of her previous arrest,

13:43.303 --> 13:46.064
the fingerprints were on file.

13:46.473 --> 13:49.308
What's next then?

13:49.343 --> 13:50.532
We're gonna fight this, right?

13:50.552 --> 13:52.729
- Yeah.
- It wasn't even Daphne's idea.

13:52.749 --> 13:54.247
All she did was spray some paint.

13:54.281 --> 13:57.116
I know, but the lawyer doesn't
like our chances at trial.

13:57.151 --> 13:59.952
And the arraignment is scheduled
for the day after tomorrow,

13:59.987 --> 14:02.050
so she needs an answer soon.

14:05.289 --> 14:06.859
We've gotta do something.

14:06.894 --> 14:08.661
I can make more calls.
I can call in a favor.

14:08.695 --> 14:10.414
It's just one lawyer, get another.

14:10.434 --> 14:11.964
- Kathryn: We need to find a better lawyer.
- What are you talking about?

14:11.999 --> 14:14.248
Find another lawyer.
We can't just let her go to prison.

14:14.268 --> 14:16.936
- John: We have the best lawyer...
- Just stop.

14:17.897 --> 14:21.153
I appreciate everyone trying to help.
I really do.

14:21.173 --> 14:24.577
And maybe if I had listened to some
of you and not been so stubborn,

14:24.611 --> 14:26.746
we wouldn't all be here right now,

14:26.780 --> 14:29.565
but I can't change that now.

14:29.838 --> 14:32.345
I've made a decision.

14:32.881 --> 14:35.040
I'm gonna take the plea deal.

14:35.060 --> 14:37.490
This isn't like when you
blackmailed Chip Coto.

14:37.524 --> 14:39.459
You have a record. You'll go to prison.

14:39.493 --> 14:41.816
I need to face up to what I've done,

14:41.836 --> 14:43.785
whatever the consequences.

14:46.018 --> 14:48.810
I want us all to enjoy graduation,

14:48.830 --> 14:50.808
like we're supposed to.

14:52.111 --> 14:53.588
Can we do that?

14:57.177 --> 15:01.643
I just want one last day with you
guys before everything changes.

15:04.199 --> 15:05.885
Now if you'll excuse me,

15:05.919 --> 15:09.467
I have a graduation speech to finish.

15:25.164 --> 15:26.416
(Door opens)

15:26.436 --> 15:30.574
Hey, shouldn't you be getting
ready for your big day?

15:30.594 --> 15:32.679
I need to talk to you about something.

15:32.877 --> 15:33.907
Of course.

15:33.927 --> 15:37.672
Okay, I don't want to seem insensitive

15:37.692 --> 15:40.503
with everything that's
happening with Daphne right now.

15:40.523 --> 15:41.819
It's all right.

15:41.839 --> 15:45.249
We're not gonna ignore you.
What's going on?

15:45.269 --> 15:48.891
Emmett's going to USC in the fall,
and I want to go with him.

15:48.925 --> 15:50.959
And I asked my parents

15:50.994 --> 15:53.527
and my dad was really against it.

15:53.547 --> 15:56.071
I can see why he's concerned.

15:56.091 --> 15:58.033
L.A. is a long way away.

15:58.068 --> 16:02.340
That's what he said, but he also said
that if I put together a good plan,

16:02.360 --> 16:04.383
they'd be okay with me going.

16:04.544 --> 16:06.025
And did you?

16:06.045 --> 16:09.153
I lined up a job bussing
cafeteria tables at l.A.C.M.A.

16:09.173 --> 16:11.979
I found a safe, cheap apartment.

16:11.999 --> 16:15.094
Emmett is gonna sell his motorcycle
so we can buy a small car to share,

16:15.114 --> 16:17.886
and I even signed up for some
extension courses at Cal arts,

16:17.906 --> 16:20.969
which is this amazing art school.

16:22.048 --> 16:25.076
Sounds like you've done your homework.

16:25.957 --> 16:27.620
What's stopping you?

16:28.191 --> 16:30.157
I'm gonna need some money to get started.

16:30.177 --> 16:33.168
First and last month's rent
and some travel expenses.

16:33.203 --> 16:35.404
It's a little under $5,000.

16:35.438 --> 16:37.363
I was wondering if I could
use some of the money

16:37.383 --> 16:40.515
that Angelo left me to cover that.

16:46.289 --> 16:48.138
I'm proud of you.

16:49.714 --> 16:51.803
I think Angelo would be too.

16:51.823 --> 16:55.680
Is... is that a "yes?"

16:56.834 --> 16:58.216
It is.

16:58.236 --> 17:00.971
Thank you. Oh, thank you.

17:00.991 --> 17:02.898
Thank you for trusting me.

17:07.836 --> 17:09.570
Wow.

17:11.674 --> 17:14.390
- For you.
- What is this?

17:14.410 --> 17:17.232
My realistic plan.
My budget, travel expenses,

17:17.252 --> 17:20.954
housing, transportation,
and my work income, all the details.

17:20.973 --> 17:22.518
Wait a second. You have a job?

17:22.551 --> 17:25.135
At the L.A. County Museum of Art.

17:25.155 --> 17:26.892
- What about the...
- Start-up expenses?

17:26.912 --> 17:29.591
You'll find all those details in column
"b."

17:29.626 --> 17:31.560
How are you gonna pay for
the start-up expenses?

17:31.594 --> 17:35.164
Regina is letting me have some
of the money that Angelo left me.

17:35.198 --> 17:36.997
So I'm all set.

17:37.767 --> 17:40.269
Well, it seems your daughter
is intent on revisiting

17:40.303 --> 17:42.037
her notion of moving to L.A.

17:42.071 --> 17:43.959
Why do I have a bill for you

17:43.979 --> 17:46.839
from Dr. Larkin for an MRI?

17:47.323 --> 17:48.911
Okay, don't freak out.

17:48.945 --> 17:52.589
It turns out, like Angelo,
I have the genetic disposition

17:52.609 --> 17:54.149
towards developing an aneurysm.

17:54.184 --> 17:56.151
- Oh, my God.
- What? You have an aneurysm?

17:56.186 --> 17:57.219
How did you find out?
Why didn't you tell us?

17:57.253 --> 17:58.720
Do you have any idea how
dangerous that could be?

17:58.755 --> 18:00.574
Okay, hold on. Just let me explain.

18:01.024 --> 18:03.147
I don't have an aneurysm.

18:03.167 --> 18:06.176
But that doesn't mean I
won't develop one later on.

18:06.196 --> 18:08.797
I found out when we went to
Chicago to meet my cousin.

18:08.832 --> 18:12.000
It turns out Angelo had a sister

18:12.035 --> 18:14.262
who died of an aneurysm, too,

18:14.282 --> 18:16.129
which is why I got tested by Dr. Larkin.

18:16.149 --> 18:17.873
And I'm gonna continue
to get tested regularly,

18:17.907 --> 18:19.741
but right now, that's all I can do.

18:19.776 --> 18:21.677
And I've made my peace with it.

18:21.711 --> 18:24.813
You could have had an aneurysm
and you didn't even tell us.

18:24.848 --> 18:27.449
I didn't tell you because
I knew you would worry

18:27.483 --> 18:28.909
and that's not gonna change anything.

18:28.929 --> 18:30.586
I didn't wanna put you guys through that.

18:30.620 --> 18:32.904
Keeping us out of the
loop shows immaturity, which is why

18:32.924 --> 18:35.657
- you are not ready to go to L.A.
- You're not going.

18:35.692 --> 18:39.328
I wanted your blessing, but I'm 18 now,
and I really don't need it.

18:39.362 --> 18:41.372
I am going.

18:56.048 --> 18:58.624
Who would've thought that
we would end up graduating

18:58.644 --> 19:00.816
from the same school?

19:01.051 --> 19:03.967
Three years ago,
I didn't even know you existed.

19:04.576 --> 19:07.430
And I had never heard of Carlton.

19:08.348 --> 19:12.060
Do you remember that day?
The day we first met?

19:12.338 --> 19:15.118
I was so jealous of you back then.

19:16.843 --> 19:21.094
Now you're the one with
the perfect boyfriend.

19:21.578 --> 19:23.839
The perfect life next year in L.A.

19:24.098 --> 19:26.468
- Stop.
- No, it's true.

19:26.488 --> 19:29.878
You handled everything so
well after Angelo died.

19:30.213 --> 19:32.497
Daphne, I...

